%I A098807 #14 Mar 17 2026 04:09:35
%S A098807 2,4,6,8,10,12,14,18,20,24,28,30,34,36,38,40,42,48,50,54,60,64,66,68,
%T A098807 72,78,80,84,90,94,96,98,102,104,108,110,114,120,124,126,132,134,138,
%U A098807 144,150,154,156,162,164,168,174,178,180,186,188,190,192,198,204,208,210
%N A098807 Numbers k such that there exists a prime p for which p - k and p + k are also prime.
%C A098807 From _Robert Israel_, Mar 16 2026: (Start)
%C A098807 All terms are even.
%C A098807 Dickson's Conjecture implies that all multiples of 6 are terms.
%C A098807 An even number k not divisible by 3 is a term if and only if k + 3 and 2*k + 3 are primes. (End)
%H A098807 Robert Israel, <a href="/A098807/b098807.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%e A098807 a(4) = 8 is a term because p = 11, p - 8 = 3 and p + 8 = 19 are primes. - _Robert Israel_, Mar 16 2026
%p A098807 filter:= proc(k)
%p A098807 k mod 3 = 0 or (isprime(k + 3) and isprime(2*k+3))
%p A098807 end proc:
%p A098807 select(filter, [seq(i,i=2..1000,2)]); # _Robert Israel_, Mar 16 2026
%Y A098807 Cf. A098806.
%K A098807 easy,nonn
%O A098807 1,1
